        <body>       
                 
                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>My dear Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>Many thanks for your note<lb/> and dispatch.<lb/></p>
            <p>The cremation of Mrs Horener<lb/> &#40;n&#233;e Nathan&#41; took place in Milan some days<lb/> ago and they are bringing the body here for<lb/> interment.  Her brother&#44; Julian Nathan&#44; has<lb/> applied for permission to bury her remains<lb/> in our ground or in the family plot.<lb/></p>
            <p>The trustees wish your opinion as well as mine&#44;&#45;&#45;<lb/> on these questions<lb/></p>
            <p>1. Is cremation prohibited or not by Jewish Law.<lb/></p>
            <p>2. Ought we to bury the remains in our burial grounds&#63;<lb/></p>
            <p>I replied it is against the spirit of Jewish Law<lb/> and we ought to bury the remains&#44;&#45;&#45;&#91;Hebrew&#93; if deemed desirable<lb/> for the purpose of discouraging cremation.<lb/></p>
            <p>And I said you concurred.  But they wish your<lb/> opinion direct.  Will you kindly write it to me.<lb/>  If I misinterpreted you&#44; do not hesitate to say so.<lb/>  Awaiting your reply&#44; yrs H Pereira Mendes<lb/></p>
                
            <p>We cannot get the applicants by Thursday.  We must announce in papers.  <sic>Untill</sic> I hear from you to the<lb/> contrary&#44; I will announce next Sunday as the day for examination.  Please write therefore at once.<lb/></p>
                
            <p>You <hi rend="underline">must</hi> be present for the examination<lb/> of students and Dr Liebermann.  I would<lb/> sooner put it off than have you<lb/> absent.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
